caption: Absolutely amazing coffee - I always get an expertly done latte here, friendly staff, and great filipino treats (delicious cassava cake! have ordered this at least 5 different times, always perfection!), also loved the taro latte. This little place is amazing. I love them. It’s my neighborhood coffee shop, I go there every morning. Always 10/10 food, drink, and snacks. Plus it’s a good source for Korean/Asian foods and ingredients. Would recommend to anyone

Lovely little spot. Great coffee, but even better food. This little breakfast sandwich with sausage and banana ketchup is amazing. Never seems to be too crowded when I drop in either.

Coffee's great, food is delicious hearty Filipino breakfast fare ie indulgent Tapsilog and Longsilog for days (don't panic vegans they do a beautiful elaborated avo toast), and for desserts they have the best ube ensaymada and cassava cake in New York, made in house!

A welcoming and charming cafe with amazing coffee, and an expansive espresso + tea menu. The Taro latte is a must try when you want more than your usual coffee.  The family run establishment *also* has delicious Filipino breakfast treats. My favorite is the pork longanissa! A bonus is being able to see them put everything together. Everything is delicious and made with love.  My favorite morning spot in the neighborhood. Grab a book, and chill in the am at this spot.
Joe's brown butter chocolate chip cookie is no joke...💪🏽

My second home - one of the best neighborhood cafes I know. It’s comfy, the staff is super friendly, the WiFi is fast, the music is good (including once some cool Filipino jazz pop that I now have on my own playlists), and the food is creative and awesome. AND they serve tea in these wonderful big fat mugs that just make you feel better (and with a spoon and plate to take the tea bag out - idk why this isn’t a thing everyone does, but oh well).  Try the Ube Brioche, and also the avocado toast - it might be one of the best in Brooklyn.
Spent my morning with chai latte amd a sausage sandwich with familiar filipino ingredients boosted my morning start! A chill place with a friendly staff.

Wow. That egg sandwich is BOMB. The juicy umami frittata, runny egg (how it should be), and kick from the banana ketchup work perfectly together for an excellent sandwich. The bread was a little soggy but the overall flavor of the sandwich more than make up for it.  The filter coffee also had personality, with some notes of cocoa towards the end of the cup.  Although I took my order to go, the place has a cozy and chill— yet not crammed— vibe, though the decor could use a little update.

This is a small local Cafe in Williamsburg. If you're looking for a different ambiance this is your spot. They make delicious homemade Filipino desserts and they're coffee is imported from the Philippines. The owner is very warm and friendly he sat with us and gave us food compliments and started a small chat. Nice, cozy place and I would come back every week. Having breakfast here just feels like you're back in the Philippines.
Love the ensaimada and my daughter also does now too
Cute little shop serving City of Saint's coffee and some Filipino sweets, I love the taro bun! As well they has tasty grain bowls and egg sammies. Good tunes and vibes from the crew on past visits.

Easily one of my favourite coffee shops. It is no doubt that they have a perfect 5 stars. Everything they do is 10+!  Mountain Province is a short step from my office so naturally I buy my coffees, muffins and sometimes take up there space to do some work.  The vibe and friendliness of the staff is so awesome. They greet you with huge hellos and get to know you and the coffee you like really fast. (Also very reasonably priced) I've ordered the egg sandwich on a scone. Holy crap it's superb. They use a spicy banana tomato ketchup, it gives the sandwich an awesome kick. The avocado toast is also really great and filling.  The space is small and cozy but as soon as you walk in you feel like home.  I definitely recommend this awesome spot for great strong coffee and delicious all day eats.

Best coffee in my whole entire fall season is found here. Place: It doesn't have very big sign so you have to find it carefully. Not much of decoration yet it is cozy little place.  Coffee: Latte was perfect! I like my latte to be soft and creamy and it was at its best and size was slightly bigger than other place (I think it was 16oz)  Food: I tried coconut muffin, and It was like nothing else in the planet. I really liked the real coconut on top of my muffin and overall It just was awesome.  Service: people were really welcoming and friendly.

Loved the coffee, baked goods and the atmosphere. Owners are friendly and have made Mountain Province a great place for starting your day or dropping in for a quiet place to work or relax.
